The paper discusses learning probabilistic logic programming languages, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The algorithm SLIPCOVER is used for structure learning, which involves searching and optimizing the space of probabilistic clauses and theories (cs.LG). The paper also mentions using the log likelihood of data as a guiding heuristic, which is a common approach in natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The datasets used in the experiments are real-world datasets, which suggests a focus on practical applications and data management (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses comparing SLIPCOVER with other algorithms for learning logic programs, which suggests a focus on software engineering and programming languages (cs.SE).
